TY  - JOUR
TI  - Horizon in a Simple Model of Economic Growth
AU  - Keeler, Emmett
AB  - [In long-run planning, targets may be set further in the future than economic technologies can be estimated. How costly in hindsight is limited foresight? Following Łos, we say k is an ε-horizon if knowledge of economic possibilities for the next K time periods permits decisions with results at most ε worse than optimal. For a dynamic Leontief model, we show that any T-period efficient path is almost as big as all feasible T-period paths during the first T - K periods. Thus, given K periods notice, we can plan an ε-optimal growth path no matter how technologies change after T.]
